<HEADLINE>
EDITORS: 
</HEADLINE>
  
 July 3, 1998      The Hearst News Service has filed this story for Saturday in the
``i'' category:
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLINTON-CHINA (Hong Kong) _ President Clinton ended a nine-day
visit to China Friday with the prediction that democracy would
replace the hard-nosed communist regime that has ruled in Beijing
since 1949. The president also lavished praise on Chinese President
Jiang Zemin in laudatory remarks that may ignite critics back home
who challenge his dealings with Beijing as a naive, one-way street.
By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
