</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, June 25, the House voted 402-8, to pass an IRS
overhaul and tax bill. The measure would establish a citizens'
oversight panel and increase taxpayer rights in collection disputes
with the IRS. Supporters said the bill would protect taxpayers from
any abuse from the tax agency. Opponents objected to a measure that
shortens the capital gains holding period from 18 months to 12
months to escape financial penalties, calling it a tax break for
the wealthy. A ``yes'' vote favors the bill.
