<HEADER>
A9550 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MUSIC-SPICE-2ND &LR;  &UR; TAKE     07-03 1073
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MUSIC-SPICE-2ND </SLUG>
   TAKE-BOS  
 UNDATED: ... your first.  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   A: Definitely, but I think not a lot of people realize that our
first act on television, which was on MTV, was live. And I think a
lot of people missed that, and since then we've done lots of stuff
live. So, this show, we were just talking about it a minute ago
with the girls, we feel that the Americans are really going to
appreciate this because it is filled with entertainment. A little
bit like a musical and put different elements and vibes and just
different things on. Hopefully, the Americans will really
appreciate it.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I imagine that as much negative attention that you've gotten
from some of the elements of the rock press there's probably some
aspect of a guilty pleasure working for some of the older people
who are there with their kids. Do you think so?
</P>
<P>
   A: Well, actually, every single night is very funny. We're very
pleased because a lot of families come, the moms and the dads and
the sons and the daughters. At the beginning of the show, you see
the dads sitting there and they're sort of trying to be a bit cool
and they're just sitting there with their kids going, ``Oh, yes,
calm down.'' And by the end of the show, the dads are the worst!
They're up and they're dancing and they're singing all the words.
They're dancing away and they know all the words and they're doing
the routines.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Well, I think it allows the dads to induldge in a little bit
of, uh, fantasy too.
</P>
<P>
   A: Oh, maybe, but I don't know about that!
</P>
<P>
   Q: Right. Maybe that's something you can't answer ...
</P>
<P>
   A: Yeah, I wouldn't answer that one.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I should ask you, too, because people float these sort of
accusations: Is there lip-synching involved, backing tapes?
</P>
<P>
   A: Not at all, the whole show is absolutely live. We're quite
proud of that. It's something we've been waiting to do, to sing
live. And obviously to prove ourselves a little bit. The whole show
is very live indeed.
</P>
<P>
   Q: People also suggest you don't write your material. Do you?
</P>
<P>
   A: Yeah, we write absolutely all of it. We work with producers,
who actually write most of the music because we haven't got time to
go into a studio and work all that side out. But we actually write
all of the lyrics, we do all of the melodies. We do like to say
it's 50/50 because obviously it can get very messy. So, we'll we
want this kind of bass line or we want that ... The producers that
we work with are very good friends of ours who we've worked with
since day one. It's been a really good collaboration. ... At the
end of the day, I can't sit there every second saying, ``We do our
own music, we do sing live,'' You know, you can't keep shouting
about it all the time.
</P>
<P>
   If you actually read the back of our CD, it says ``written by
the Spice Girls.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: We should discuss the rumors of a Spice Girls breakup, and
the firing of your manager, Simon. Did you consider breaking up?
</P>
<P>
   A: Not at all. (As to Simon) I can't go too much into detail
with it because of legal sides. But the whole thing with Simon was
we'd actually managed ourselves for a year before we met him. We'd
written our first album, we went to him with our first album as the
Spice Girls. I think it was just a thing where we felt like we
needed to move on..
</P>
<P>
   Q: There was also the rumor of you and he having an affair.
</P>
<P>
   A: Oh, no. You realize, when you've been in the press every
single day how much of it is lies. Sometimes I can't quite believe
what is said but, no, that was so very untrue. I think because we
had a man behind us up until that point, for five girls to go off
and do their own thing was a little bit, ``Oh, are you sure about
that?'' But we have done and we're really proud of that and we're
doing quite well.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is there room in the Spice Girls world for anything that
isn't upbeat and optimistic?
</P>
<P>
   A: I think, yeah. When all five of us sit down, we do come out
with _ like we've had days where and we're all really tired and
we've written some gorgeous songs. There's a beautiful song on our
second album, ``Take Me Home.'' But we do realize that not
everything is so positive. And we've got some very deep songs. And,
actually, in the upbeat stuff, if you listen to the lyrics, some of
them are very, very deep.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Although, I don't think you'd ever be confused with, say, Joy
Division.
</P>
<P>
   A: I don't think that. I think they were great. People take to
music differently, and I do completely identify with the people who
write about real life and what they've been through. But with the
Spice Girls, we feel like for kids these days there's so much
negativity in the world, we just want to give them a bit of hope
and a bit of positivity, really.
</P>
<P>
   Q: In England, you guys do ads for so many things. In a certain
sense, it seems like you're a commodity yourself.
</P>
<P>
   A: I think every band in some way does publicity, and for us, at
the end of the day, we are more than just a girl band: We've done
films, we've done adverts, and that's what we enjoy. We would never
do anything that we didn't agree with.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Do you ever worry about a glut of Spice Girls related
products?
</P>
<P>
   A: What do you mean a glut?
</P>
<P>
   Q: Uh, too many. Like, enough where people go ``Oh, my God yet
another one!''
</P>
<P>
   A: Umm, not really, because we never take anything too
seriously. We're having fun with that and we enjoy doing it and
we're not hurting anybody. There have been things that we've turned
down, and then there's things that we've really enjoyed doing.
We've sat down and thought about that quite carefully.
</P>
<P>
   Q: So, I'm gathering that you can sleep at night?
</P>
<P>
   A: Oh, yes, definitely.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Plucked off the Virgin Records website:
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
SPICE GIRLS STATEMENT:
</P>
<P>
   We are upset and saddened by Geri's departure but we are very
supportive in whatever she wants to do. The Spice Girls are here to
stay _ see you at the stadiums! We are sorry for all our fans for
havng to go through this.
</P>
<P>
   All our love,
</P>
<P>
   Victoria
</P>
<P>
   Emma
</P>
<P>
   Mel C
</P>
<P>
   Mel B
</P>
<P>
   STATEMENT FROM GERI HALLIWELL:
</P>
<P>
   This message is for the fans:
</P>
<P>
   Sadly, I would like to confirm I have left the Spice Girls. This
is because of differences between us. I'm sure the group will
continue to be successful and I wish them all the best. I have no
immediate plans. I wish to apologise (sic) to all the fans and
thank them and everyone who's been there.
</P>
<P>
   Lots of love,
</P>
<P>
   Geri
</P>
<P>
   P.S. I'll be back.
</P>
