   FLA-FIRES (Daytona Beach, Fla.) _ All 30,000 resident of Flagler
County were ordered to leave Friday as wildfires showed no sign of
ending their six-week romp through northeast Florida. Frightened
evacuees cried and crowded the roads out of town. By Mireya
Navarro. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-CLINTON (Hong Kong) _ President Clinton Friday called
Jiang Zemin, the president of China, a visionary leader who could
be the figure who brings China to democracy. Clinton, in a news
conference that closed his nine-day trip to China, gave what
amounted to a vigorous personal endorsement of the Chinese
president, saying Jiang had the imagination needed to transform
China from a single-party Communist state to a pluralistic
democracy. By John M. Broder.
</P>
