<P>
   Under the Mirvishes, the theater staged 80 plays, with
particular successes during the artistic directorship of Jonathan
Miller from 1987 to 1990 and the recent revival of the classical
repertory under Sir Peter Hall.
</P>
<P>
   ``All theatergoers love the Old Vic for its place in the history
of British theater,'' Bernstein said after signing the deal
Thursday. ``Our task is to ensure its future becomes as important
as its past.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-03-98 1912EDT &QL; 
