<P>
   Continental Express recently needed tractors that could push at
least 50,000 pounds, and much more in inclement weather. Large
tractors made by Harlan competitors would do the job but at a cost
near $100,000. The smaller Harlan tractors then being made were
cheaper but not large enough.
