<SLUG> BC-BRAVES-ONDECK04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On Deck: New York Mets
 &HT;    ByThomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:10 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: TBS; 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: RHP Kevin Millwood (9-4, 4.78; 0-0,
18.00 ERA vs. Mets) vs. RHP Masato Yoshii (4-3, 3.45; first
appearance vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Millwood, making his first start in 10 days after his
turn was skipped, is having his roughest stretch since joining the
club last July 12. In two starts against Montreal and the New York
Yankees, he lasted a total of 4 2/3 innings and gave up 14 hits
(three homers and two doubles) and 12 earned runs. His curveball
has been particularly vulnerable. Since going 7-1 in his first 10
outings, Millwood has since gone 2-3, accumulating an 8.87 ERA
since May 30. His only previous appearance against the Mets was an
unfortunate spot of relief work on the last day of the 1997 season,
when he gave up four hits and two runs. He has not pitched in
relief since. Yoshii, 33, came to the Mets as a free agent last
January after accumulating a 73-51 record in 13 seasons in the
Japan League. He was a teammate of Hideo Nomo for five years in
Kinetseu. Like Nomo, he throws the forkball, although after an
excellent start (4-1, 2.33 ERA through first nine games), the
league may be solving him. He is 0-2 in his last six starts with a
5.79 ERA.
</P>
